<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="420" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">662.6331/69</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State of a
                                Conversation With the Italian Ambassador</hi> (<hi rend="italic">De
                                Martino</hi>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-26">March 26, 1931</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>During the call today of the Italian Ambassador he brought up the
                            question of the customs union. I told him that I had had nothing <pb facs="0685" n="571" xml:id="pg_571"/> to say on that subject and
                            neither had the Department of Commerce and that reports to the contrary
                            were inaccurate. He said he understood that. He further stated that
                            Italy had been inclined to favor it but that was merely tentative.</p>
                        <closer><signed>H[<hi rend="smallcaps">enry</hi>] L. S[<hi rend="smallcaps">timson</hi>]</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>